        "RATHSKELLER": "Orig., in Germany, the cellar or basement of the city hall,usually rented for use as a restaurant where beer is sold; hence, abeer saloon of the German type below the street level, where,usually, drinks are served only at tables and simple food may also behad; -- sometimes loosely used, in English, of what are essentiallybasement restaurants where liquors are served.",
        "RATIFICATION": "The act of ratifying; the state of being ratified;confirmation; sanction; as, the ratification of a treaty.",
