        "RAZOR": "A task of a wild boar. Razor fish. (Zoöl.) (a) A smallMediterranean fish (Coryphæna novacula), prized for the table. (b)The razor shell.-- Razor grass (Bot.), a West Indian plant (Scleria scindens), thetriangular stem and the leaves of which are edged with minute sharpteeth.-- Razor grinder (Zoöl.), the European goat-sucker.-- Razor shell (Zoöl.), any marine bivalve shell belonging to Solenand allied genera, especially Solen, or Ensatella, ensis, andAmericana, which have a long, narrow, somewhat curved shell,resembling a razor handle in shape. Called also rasor clam, razorfish, knife handle.-- Razor stone. Same as Novaculite.-- Razor strap, or razor strop, a strap or strop used in sharpeningrazors.",
