        "REPRODUCE": "To produce again. Especially:(a) To bring forward again; as, to reproduce a witness; to reproducecharges; to reproduce a play.(b) To cause to exist again.Those colors are unchangeable, and whenever all those rays with thosetheir colors are mixed again they reproduce the same white light asbefore. Sir I. Newton.",
        "REPRODUCER": "One who, or that which, reproduces. Burke.",
        "REPRODUCTION": "the process by which plants and animals give rise to offspring.",
