        "ROSEOLA": "A rose-colored efflorescence upon the skin, occurring incircumscribed patches of little or no elevation and often alternatelyfading and reviving; also, an acute specific disease which ischaracterized by an eruption of this character; -- called also roserash.-- Ro*se\"o*lous, a.",
